pageContext.claim: “Fact check: @realDonaldTrump kicked the Nazi out of NYC after 14 years and multiple Presidents allowed him to stay.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is exaggerating his role here. No president "allowed him to stay." Rather after a federal immigration judge ordered he be deported in 2004, American officials failed to convince any country to accept him.  Trump can claim credit for securing the deportation of 95-year old Jakiw Palij.
